/****************/
/*Setting up AP */
/****************/
This section explains how to install hostapd and dhcp server and configure them to setup
an access point in infrastructure mode.

*Install hostapd
$sudo apt-get install hostapd

*Install dhcp server that assigns IP address to connecting clients
$sudo apt-get install dhcp3-server

*Open one terminal. Do not close this terminal.
*Set current directory to <src-root>/scripts
$sudo chmod a+x hostap-setup.sh
$./hostap-setup.sh

*Open another terminal
*Set current directory to <src-root>/scripts
$sudo chmod a+x dhcpd-setup.sh
$./dhcpd-setup.sh


